atter suits you, please let me know at once. I am leaving for Davos on the 18th but the Montreux-Palace will forward anything.

Best regards.





Vladimir Nabokov





TO: GLENN COLLINS

TL (XEROX), 1 p.





Montreux-Palace Hotel

1820 Montreux, Switzerland

August 20, 1975

Dear Mr. Collins,

I had been looking forward eagerly to that delightful essay. For more than a month I hunted butterflies around Davos. Then I took a bad tumble down a steep slippery slope and was laid up for several days